cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.DB 

This paper deals with the problem of gaining knowledge by reverse engineering peer ranking services, which is related to social network analysis and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper also involves some aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and database systems (cs.DB) since it deals with the manipulation of user profiles and the impact of topological metrics on the rankings. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) since it deals with the algorithms used to rank users based on their online activity.
